{{define "welcome"}}
<p class="t-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:0.25rem;">Setup</p>
<h2 class="t-h2" style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Welcome</h2>
<p class="t-body" style="color:rgb(var(--muted));margin-bottom:1rem;">
  This wizard will configure your control panel. You'll provide database
  credentials (local or external MariaDB/MySQL), create an admin user,
  set the panel URL, optionally configure SMTP, and register your first
  Caddy proxy node.
</p>
<ul class="t-small" style="color:rgb(var(--muted));margin-bottom:1.5rem;list-style:disc;padding-left:1.25rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.25rem;">
  <li>Have your DB host, port, user, and password ready.</li>
  <li>Use external managed DB or the bundled <code>mariadb</code> service.</li>
  <li>Pick a strong admin password (Argon2id-hashed at rest).</li>
  <li>Caddy node Admin API must be reachable from the app container.</li>
</ul>
<form method="POST" action="/install/start" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">
  <div>
    <label class="t-small" style="display:block;font-weight:500;margin-bottom:0.375rem;" for="install_token">Install token</label>
    <input id="install_token" name="install_token" type="text" autocomplete="off" class="r-input"
           style="font-family:monospace;"
           placeholder="paste the value of INSTALL_TOKEN env var here">
    <p class="t-caption" style="color:rgb(var(--muted));margin-top:0.375rem;">
      The panel ships locked. Paste the <code>INSTALL_TOKEN</code> you set in
      <code>.env</code> (or leave empty if connecting from <code>127.0.0.1</code>).
      Stored in a strict-SameSite cookie for the wizard duration.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div style="display:flex;justify-content:flex-end;">
    <button class="r-btn-primary" type="submit">Start setup &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</form>
{{end}}
